<subSubSection id="2DF0ACA1FFFBFFC4FF71F971FCE4F873" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="description">
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFFBFFC4FF71F971FD77F913" blockId="19.[151,1437,1662,2013]" box="[151,650,1699,1725]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
(
<figureCitation id="FDD1E3AFFFFBFFC4FF79F971FF05F913" box="[159,248,1699,1725]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="67.[151,250,1945,1969]" captionTargetBox="[193,1394,196,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-19@67.[184,1403,181,1922]" captionTargetPageId="67" captionText="FIGURE 14. Southeast Asian Eudocima and Eudocima tyrannus group adults (dorsal aspect)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605535" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605535/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Figs 14</figureCitation>
: C–D, 21: E, 26: L–N, 32: E, 93: E)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFFBFFC4FF71F915FCE4F873" blockId="19.[151,1437,1662,2013]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
The PM and apical lines are fused across from the reniform creating the appearance of a single oblique line abruptly bending towards the inner margin. In 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFBFFC4FDA0F939FD36F8AA" baseAuthorityName="Guenee" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[582,715,1771,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tyrannus">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFBFFC4FDA0F939FDAAF8AA" box="[582,599,1771,1796]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFBFFC4FD80F939FD36F8AA" box="[614,715,1771,1796]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">tyrannus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFBFFC4FD2DF939FCA5F8AA" box="[715,856,1771,1796]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
, 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFBFFC4FD31F939FCA5F8AA" baseAuthorityName="Banziger &amp; Honey" baseAuthorityYear="1984" box="[727,856,1771,1796]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurantia">E. aurantia</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFBFFC4FC74F939FBCEF8AB" baseAuthorityName="Butler" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[914,1075,1771,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sikhimensis">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFBFFC4FC74F939FBCEF8AB" box="[914,1075,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">E. sikhimensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
there is no distinct bend in this line across from the reniform. The forewing has a distinctly less pronounced tornal hook and has more green flecks versus 
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFBFFC4FF0FF8E1FE88F8E2" box="[233,373,1843,1868]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFBFFC4FF0FF8E1FE8CF8E2" baseAuthorityName="Guenee" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[233,369,1843,1868]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tyrannus">E. tyrannus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The forewings have a less prominent anal flap, and the hindwings have a more distally set hindwing marginal band than either 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFBFFC4FDDFF885FD41F8DE" baseAuthorityName="Guenee" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[569,700,1879,1904]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tyrannus">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFBFFC4FDDFF885FD41F8DE" box="[569,700,1879,1904]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">E. tyrannus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFBFFC4FD00F885FB5CF8DF" authority="(Banziger &amp; Honey 1984)" baseAuthorityName="Banziger &amp; Honey" baseAuthorityYear="1984" box="[742,1185,1879,1905]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurantia">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFBFFC4FD00F885FC95F8DE" box="[742,872,1879,1904]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">E. aurantia</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="017B82DBFFFBFFC4FC9FF885FB65F8DF" author="Banziger, H. &amp; Honey, M. R." box="[889,1176,1879,1905]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="173 - 177" refId="ref35774" refString="Banziger, H. &amp; Honey, M. R. (1984) Description of Adris suthepensis n. sp., a suspected fruit-piercing (Lepidoptera: Noctuidae) from N. Thailand and contiguous mountain regions. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft, Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique Suisse, 57, 173 - 177." type="journal article" year="1984">Bänziger &amp; Honey 1984</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The ventral marginal hindwing band is clearly separated at the veins compared to the continuous band in 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFBFFC4FBD3F8A9FB48F83A" baseAuthorityName="Guenee" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[1077,1205,1915,1940]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tyrannus">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFBFFC4FBD3F8A9FB48F83A" box="[1077,1205,1915,1940]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">E. tyrannus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFBFFC4FB25F8A9FA7EF83B" baseAuthorityName="Okano" baseAuthorityYear="1964" box="[1219,1411,1915,1941]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="okurai">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFBFFC4FB25F8A9FA7EF83B" box="[1219,1411,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Eudocima okurai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found in the southeastern Himalayas, northeast 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFFBFFC4FD42F84DFD1DF817" box="[676,736,1951,1977]" name="India" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFFBFFC4FD0CF84DFCC3F817" box="[746,830,1951,1977]" name="Bhutan" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Bhutan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFFBFFC4FCAEF84DFC4AF817" box="[840,951,1951,1977]" name="Myanmar" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFFBFFC4FC26F84DFBDBF817" box="[960,1062,1951,1977]" name="Thailand" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, northwest 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFFBFFC4FB42F84DFAF6F817" box="[1188,1291,1951,1977]" name="Malaysia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
at elevations of 
<quantity id="A21252CFFFFBFFC4FF50F811FEACF873" box="[182,337,1987,2013]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" metricValueMax="1.7" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="m" value="1450.0" valueMax="1700.0" valueMin="1200.0">1200–1700 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation id="017B82DBFFFBFFC4FEB9F811FD89F873" author="Banziger, H. &amp; Honey, M. R." box="[351,628,1987,2013]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="173 - 177" refId="ref35774" refString="Banziger, H. &amp; Honey, M. R. (1984) Description of Adris suthepensis n. sp., a suspected fruit-piercing (Lepidoptera: Noctuidae) from N. Thailand and contiguous mountain regions. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft, Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique Suisse, 57, 173 - 177." type="journal article" year="1984">Bänziger &amp; Honey 1984</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFFBFFC4FD54F811FCE8F873" box="[690,789,1987,2013]" name="Vietnam" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
